 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of state.
     
     The state observed module identifies an observed state, which may be either 
     predicted or actual, and enabling it to linked to the thing or things that 
     are in the state. An observed state represents a period of time when the 
     criterium defining the state type either are or will be satisfied for one 
     or more items.  Actual observed states therefore correspond to a period in 
     the life of something. States are not limited to products but may apply to 
     activities, people, and organizations.
   </p>
 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
